PROJETO-DE-PESQUISA.NOME-DO-PROJETO: Biofertilizers production using humic acids and plant growth promoting
PROJETO-DE-PESQUISA.DESCRICAO-DO-PROJETO: The objective of this research is turn available for small farmers an biofertilizer produced with humic acids isolated from vermicompost and plant growth promoting bacteria. Humic acids and endophytic diazotrophic bacteria can stimulate root growth. The later as well can fix nitrogen, produce plant hormones and others compounds like organic acids that can solubilize unavailable phosphorus species. We will develop the technology to use simultaneously humic acids and beneficial bacteria in solution that will be delivery as foliar spray in maize crop. Experiments will be conduced at research experimental farm and on different small farmers. In parallel, under laboratory conditions, we will carried out evaluation of ion fluxes in maize seedlings treated with biofertilizer using ion-selective vibrating probe system to measure possible changes on nutrients absorption. The interation bioertilizer - maize will be studied using different microscopic approaches to localize the establishment sites into the plant body. We will expect to enhance food secutity and maize crop production under low fertility soils due plant stimulation by biofertilizers produced with humic acids and beneficial bacteria
